    • Constructor Detail

      • RoundDoubleCellFactory

        RoundDoubleCellFactory(int precision,
                       NumberMode numberMode,
                       RoundingMode roundingMode,
                       RoundDoubleConfigKeys.RoundOutputType outputType,
                       int[] colIndexToRound,
                       DataColumnSpec[] newColSpecs)
        Creates instance of RoundDoubleCellFactory with specified precision.
        Parameters:
        precision - The decimal place to round to.
        numberMode - The mode of the precision to round to (decimal place, significant figures).
        roundingMode - The mode to round the double values. additional column or if the old values will be replaced.
        outputType - Specifies whether rounded values will be represented as strings or doubles.
        colIndexToRound - The indices of the columns containing the values to round.
        newColSpecs - The specs of the new columns (replaced or appended).

    • Method Detail

      • getCells

        public DataCell[] getCells(DataRow row)
        Get the new cells for a given row. These cells are incorporated into the existing row. The way it is done is defined through the ColumnRearranger using this object.
        Parameters:
        row - The row of interest.
        Returns:
        The new cells to that row.
